Jonathan Byrd made a hole-in-one on
the first hole of a three-man playoff to win the U.S. PGA Tourâ€™s
Fall Series event in Las Vegas.   Byrd aced the 204-yard par-3 17th hole at the TPC Summerlin
to beat Cameron Percy and defending champion Martin Laird at the
Justin Timberlake Shriners Hospital Open.   Byrd received $774,000 for his fourth PGA Tour win and
